{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/blog-performance","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"1de02468-5840-56da-96f7-a8f6a77bb834","html":"<p>Recently I revamped this blog site using the amazing <a href=\"https://github.com/gatsbyjs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">GatsbyJS</a>. I noticed immediately how much faster it was, and that was in part due to how much work has gone into making gatsby produce an optimized site. I recently watched a <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?list=PLNYkxOF6rcICc687SxHQRuo9TVNOJelSZ&#x26;v=6m_E-mC0y3Y\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">video</a> by Sam Saccone and Paul Irish about performance and metrics. They spoke about two tools <a href=\"https://github.com/GoogleChrome/lighthouse\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Lighthouse</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/paulirish/pwmetrics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">PWMetrics</a> which you can use today to measure your site performance in a useful way. I was able to quickly grasp what bottlenecks were having an adverse affect on the blogs load times.</p>\n<p>Through diagnosis I was able to drastically improve the score. Here is what I get from pwmetrics today.</p>\n<p><a href=\"/media/pwmetrics.png\"><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 13.750000000000002%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAADCAYAAACTWi8uAAAACXBIWXMAABYlAAAWJQFJUiTwAAAAj0lEQVQI133MvQrCMBiF4S+paZMYTWyLg4ObFf8QqU2oKCLei4J4/+sxgiAiOjycdzo0KHI4bcHPKejOQZfo+tpbdMxA0wS0YuDDDhKKTfSbMT10tYIbVyiXO5Tz8KHYeOR17GYNN5L/z56UkkhThWqi0QYJv5UIzZuvMxxai9O+j8XMwhgLIQQ4518YY3gAb4BIy7A6iosAAAAASUVORK5CYII='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/098581d9638297dc9d27b478a5c30efc/8ac56/pwmetrics.webp 240w,\n/static/098581d9638297dc9d27b478a5c30efc/d3be9/pwmetrics.webp 480w,\n/static/098581d9638297dc9d27b478a5c30efc/e46b2/pwmetrics.webp 960w,\n/static/098581d9638297dc9d27b478a5c30efc/f992d/pwmetrics.webp 1440w,\n/static/098581d9638297dc9d27b478a5c30efc/882b9/pwmetrics.webp 1920w,\n/static/098581d9638297dc9d27b478a5c30efc/4391b/pwmetrics.webp 2380w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/098581d9638297dc9d27b478a5c30efc/8ff5a/pwmetrics.png 240w,\n/static/098581d9638297dc9d27b478a5c30efc/e85cb/pwmetrics.png 480w,\n/static/098581d9638297dc9d27b478a5c30efc/d9199/pwmetrics.png 960w,\n/static/098581d9638297dc9d27b478a5c30efc/07a9c/pwmetrics.png 1440w,\n/static/098581d9638297dc9d27b478a5c30efc/29114/pwmetrics.png 1920w,\n/static/098581d9638297dc9d27b478a5c30efc/a5120/pwmetrics.png 2380w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/098581d9638297dc9d27b478a5c30efc/d9199/pwmetrics.png\"\n          alt=\"PWMetrics\"\n          title=\"PWMetrics\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n    </span></a></p>\n<p>You can even generate it yourself. Just try out the commands below.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">yarn</span> global <span class=\"token function\">add</span> pwmetrics\npwmetrics https://vincenttaverna.com</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">yarn</span> global <span class=\"token function\">add</span> lighthouse\nlighthouse https://vincenttaverna.com</code></pre></div>\n<p>The next version of GatsbyJS, v1, is being developed right now. It will improve performance even more so, and I am really looking forward to it. Between inline CSS, offline support via service workers, and more, it will be the best release yet. If I find spare time I will definitely be contributing to it and I think you should to!</p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/blog-performance","tagSlugs":["/tag/java-script/","/tag/gatsby/","/tag/performance/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2016-11-25T02:06:00.000Z","description":"Gatsby and Metrics for the new blog.","tags":["JavaScript","Gatsby","Performance"],"title":"Blog Performance","socialImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/blog-performance"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","2857265606","401334301"]}